For when you say something's true,

130
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:11,759
even if it might make you look a little bit bad.

131
00:05:11,839 --> 00:05:13,759
And before we go on, I have to admit,

132
00:05:13,759 --> 00:05:16,399
Neil, that it was me who ate your biscuits.

133
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,120
Oh, which one?

134
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,560
The one you left on the desk.

135
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,079
Ah, that's all right.

136
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:21,920
I wasn't really keen on it anyway.

137
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,039
It had been on the floor.

138
00:05:23,039 --> 00:05:23,839
What?

139
00:05:23,839 --> 00:05:24,560
Ooh.

140
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,159
Yeah, well, serves you right.

141
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,959
And to be keen on something is our next phrase,

142
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:30,719
meaning being very interested in

143
00:05:30,719 --> 00:05:32,959
and enthusiastic about something.

144
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:35,599
Then we had to go along with something.

145
00:05:35,599 --> 00:05:37,759
This is when you were great to do something,

146
